Description: Dulle Griet. Here is Hell with representations of Sins and Sinners - to be deciphered with help of the drawings for the Seven Deadly Sins: 1) Toad for Avaritia; 2) The monster [horn?] foreshortened showing anus in front of the naked couple, and this couple underneath the harp tower - for Luxuria; 3) The monster with spoon in anus and bord in hand - for Gula (in the drawing on the right - the combination of the motifs is somewhat difficult); 4) The bird underneath the Gula monster with a plucked peacock (for Superbia) as [...] the from Luxuria; 5) Is there a bear for Ira?; 6) ~ a turkey for Invidia; 7) [Anything?] (snail) for Desidia.[scan]
